article.headline: Troy 101, N.C.-Wilmington 92
article.story: TROY, Ala. -- Richard Delk scored 28 points and Brandon Hazzard added 22 to lead Troy to a 101-92 victory over UNC-Wilmington on Monday night. Michael Volger finished with 18 points, 11 assists and six rebounds for the Trojans (5-7). Troy shot 58.7 percent for the floor (37 of 63) and went 12-of-23 shooting from beyond the arc. The Seahawks (3-9) shot 48.4 percent (31 of 64) for the game. Johnny Wolf led UNC-Wilmington with 26 points, while Jerel Stephenson scored 17 points and Chad Tomko added 14. Wilmington's Kevon Moore made two free throws to cut Troy's lead to 79-78 with 6:50 remaining. But the Trojans increased its lead to 10 points, as Delk capped the surge with a three-point play with 4:15 left to help Troy pull away.
